INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (8,1,'2010-01-22 01:43:09','2010-01-22 05:43:09','Dear MCS parents,   This Saturday we will have our first <strong>Parent Assembly (家長大會).</strong> <strong></strong> <strong>The following is the meeting agenda starting from 1:45pm</strong> 1.  Introduction of new PTA chair - Mr. Jim Yang,\r\n\r\n楊理鈞, class representatives, and new parents that just join MCS\r\n\r\n2. Introduction of school staff - Principal\r\n\r\n3. Overview of school mission &amp; status - Principal\r\n\r\n4. Detail presentation of school status, budget, and new policies - Staff\r\n\r\n5. Walk-ins\r\n\r\nThis meeting offers you the opportunity to understand school operation and to provide your inputs. Please come and show your support.\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\n\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Parent Assembly Meeting - 9/26/09 1:45pm at Parents Lounge (room 2423/2425)',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-parent-assembly-meeting-92609-145pm-at-parents-lounge-room-24232425','','','2010-01-22 01:43:09','2010-01-22 05:43:09','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=8',0,'post','',0),(9,1,'2010-01-22 01:42:40','2010-01-22 05:42:40','','MCS Parent Assembly Meeting - 9/26/09 1:45pm at Parents Lounge (room 2423/2425)',0,'','inherit','open','open','','8-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:42:40','2010-01-22 05:42:40','',8,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=9',0,'revision','',0),(10,1,'2010-01-22 01:44:19','2010-01-22 05:44:19','Dear MCS parents,   This Saturday we will have our first <strong>Parent Assembly (家長大會).</strong> <strong></strong> <strong>The following is the meeting agenda starting from 1:45pm</strong> 1.  Introduction of new PTA chair - Mr. Jim Yang,\n\n楊理鈞, class representatives, and new parents that just join MCS\n\n2. Introduction of school staff - Principal\n\n3. Overview of school mission &amp; status - Principal\n\n4. Detail presentation of school status, budget, and new policies - Staff\n\n5. Walk-ins\n\nThis meeting offers you the opportunity to understand school operation and to provide your inputs. Please come and show your support.\n\nAlex Tang\n\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Parent Assembly Meeting - 9/26/09 1:45pm at Parents Lounge (room 2423/2425)',0,'','inherit','open','open','','8-autosave','','','2010-01-22 01:44:19','2010-01-22 05:44:19','',8,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=10',0,'revision','',0),(6,1,'2010-01-22 01:38:46','2010-01-22 05:38:46','MCS parents,\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">9/22, Tuesday 7pm </span><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: DFKai-SB; color: #ff0000;\" lang=\"ZH-TW\">中華民國文化訪問團</span><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"> will perform at </span><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: DFKai-SB; color: #ff0000;\">West Bloomfield High School Auditorium</span>. This Saturday is your last chance to buy tickets at our school. Part of the ticket income from this concert will be donated to help the Taiwan people suffered from 8/8 Flood, part of the income will be used to help local Chinese school education for your kids. I strongly encourage you to participate in this wonderful event. It\'s going to be one of these unforgettable experience in your lifetime, well, at least this is how I feel.\r\n\r\nGreat News! -------- <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">MCS has a new website</span> and a new webmaster - Thanks to the great effort from our Pre-K parent Mr Steven Lien. The URL to our school can be accessed in any of the following three ways:\r\n1.  <a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.netfirms.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.michiganchineseschool.netfirms.com</a>\r\n2.  <a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>\r\n3.  <a href=\"../../\" target=\"_blank\">michiganchineseschool.org</a>.\r\n\r\nPlease visit the site and provide us your inputs. More diversified information and articles will be uploaded from time to time. We are also developing Blog function for each class so teachers and students, parents may develop more <span>communication</span> by using internet.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">This Saturday is the beginning week for our extra curricular activities</span>. Classroom 2444 is for Lego Robotics and room 2442 is for Arts. There are still spaces in the extra curriculum classes. Don\'t miss this opportunity! We will also start to register the English Writing class. Alex Wan will provide more details at school.\r\n\r\nPre-K and 1st grade parents, please note that classroom has been exchanged between this two classes.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff4040;\">9/26 is our first Parent  Assembly Meeting</span>. Please attend to show your support to the school. Information regarding to the student registration, new scholarship system, website..etc. will be presented. Don\'t miss the opportunity to participate.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">For parents elected as class representative, we will meet at parent/staff room (2423/2425) this Saturday 1:45pm to elect PTA chair</span>. Your attendance is critical to future school operation.\r\n\r\nBest regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','School communication - New website - Last call for ticket sale (9/22 concert)',0,'','publish','closed','open','','school-communication-new-website-last-call-for-ticket-sale-922-concert','','','2010-01-22 01:38:46','2010-01-22 05:38:46','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=6',0,'post','',0),(7,1,'2010-01-22 01:38:10','2010-01-22 05:38:10','','School communication - New website - Last call for ticket sale (9/22 concert)',0,'','inherit','open','open','','6-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:38:10','2010-01-22 05:38:10','',6,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=7',0,'revision','',0),(11,1,'2010-01-22 01:45:01','2010-01-22 05:45:01','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nWe held our first Parents Assembly last Saturday. About 40 parents attended this meeting. School staff presented school status and 2009-2010 budget. This semester we registered 24 new students and 84 old students. Our enrollment rate reversed the declining trend in the past few years and added 3 more students comparing to last fall. Thanks for your effort in introducing our school to your friends. This Saturday we will issue the recruiting award check at parents lounge (room 2423/2425).\r\n\r\nLast Saturday we found a cell phone at women\'s restroom opposite to room 2419. You may come to the Parent lounge this Saturday to claim it if you are the owner.\r\n\r\nWe will pass out moon cakes to every student this Saturday to celebrate <span>Chinese</span> Moon Festival. We will also show a video to tell the story of <span>Chinese</span> characters and how to practice <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy. If you are interested in <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy, this is a great opportunity for you to learn the history and the beauty of <span>Chinese</span> characters. You are welcome to bring in your <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy tools to practice following the instruction from the video. Our website also has collected some beautiful <span>Chinese</span> calligraphy pictures from the web. You may view them at <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool,org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','This Saturday Event - Michigan Chinese School (10/3/09)',0,'','publish','closed','open','','this-saturday-event-michigan-chinese-school-10309','','','2010-01-22 01:45:01','2010-01-22 05:45:01','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=11',0,'post','',0),(12,1,'2010-01-22 01:46:08','2010-01-22 05:46:08','Dear MCS parents,\n\nWe held our first Parents Assembly last Saturday. About 40 parents attended this meeting. School staff presented school status and 2009-2010 budget. This semester we registered 24 new students and 84 old students. Our enrollment rate reversed the declining trend in the past few years and added 3 more students comparing to last fall. Thanks for your effort in introducing our school to your friends. This Saturday we will issue the recruiting award check at parents lounge (room 2423/2425).\n\nLast Saturday we found a cell phone at women\'s restroom opposite to room 2419. You may come to the Parent lounge this Saturday to claim it if you are the owner.\n\nWe will pass out moon cakes to every student this Saturday to celebrate <span>Chinese</span> Moon Festival. We will also show a video to tell the story of <span>Chinese</span> characters and how to practice <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy. If you are interested in <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy, this is a great opportunity for you to learn the history and the beauty of <span>Chinese</span> characters. You are welcome to bring in your <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy tools to practice following the instruction from the video. Our website also has collected some beautiful <span>Chinese</span> calligraphy pictures from the web. You may view them at <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool,org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>\n\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS','This Saturday Event - Michigan Chinese School (10/3/09)',0,'','inherit','open','open','','11-autosave','','','2010-01-22 01:46:08','2010-01-22 05:46:08','',11,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=12',0,'revision','',0),(13,1,'2010-01-22 01:48:57','2010-01-22 05:48:57','MCS parents,\r\n\r\nParents on duty list is posted on MCS website.\r\n<div>Here is the link address of MCS Parents\' On-Duty Schedule for 2009-2010  School Year</div>\r\n<div><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/temp/MCS-2009-2010-Calendar_Parents-On-Duty.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/temp/MCS-2009-2010-Calendar_Parents-On-Duty.html</a></div>\r\nPlease review and mark your calendar accordingly.\r\n王 漢林 &amp; 呂宗龍 are parents on duty this coming Saturday. You may want to check our website from time to time for new job openings, great articles, class activities..etc..\r\n\r\nWe have several new students joined our school in the past couple of weeks. We would like to extend our welcome to the new students and new parents. Up to now we have 111 students registered. Hopefully this is the sign that Michigan economy is recovering.\r\n\r\nWe are preparing our school directory and collecting advertisements from local business. On our directory, we ask for $100 for a full page advertisement and $60 for half page. The income will help to offset the school operation cost gaps. You may contact JauYeu Lai or me  if you know anyone who maybe interested in posting advertisement on MCS directory.\r\n\r\nThis coming Saturday at parents lounge we will have some <span>Chinese</span> dish for sale from Hunan-Hunan restaurant. Here\'s the message from 双湘园的陈太太: 星期六.十七号.我想去卖些小吃.咸酥鸡.糯米肠.牛肉馅饼.\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-size-adjust: inherit; font-stretch: inherit;\" valign=\"top\">鸡肉馅饼.夫妻肺片.台湾本土泡菜.牛肉卷饼.鲜虾韭黄水饺.那天我会给大家试吃品尝.希望大家喜欢.謝謝。Don\'t miss this opportunity.\r\n\r\nTo these parents who ordered <span lang=\"ZH-CN\">粽</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">子, </span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">粽</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">子</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">將於</span>10/17 <span lang=\"ZH-CN\">星期六</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\"> </span>1:30PM <span lang=\"ZH-CN\">送到家長休息室</span>\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody></table>','MCS School Updates - 10/17/09',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-school-updates-101709','','','2010-01-22 01:48:57','2010-01-22 05:48:57','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=13',0,'post','',0),(14,1,'2010-01-22 01:48:33','2010-01-22 05:48:33','','MCS School Updates - 10/17/09',0,'','inherit','open','open','','13-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:48:33','2010-01-22 05:48:33','',13,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=14',0,'revision','',0),(15,1,'2010-01-22 01:50:03','2010-01-22 05:50:03','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nI was told recently that some students spent all recess time between classes playing video games. It\'s a distraction to their learning at school. We encourage all students to chat and play with friends during recess instead of playing video games. Please ask your kids not to bring video games to <span>Chinese</span> school.\r\n\r\nThis Saturday Hunan-Hunan restaurant will bring in \"Stinky ToFu\" and \"Stinky Pot\" for  our parents to taste and order. You may also call 313-389-0939 to order for delivery on Saturday.\r\n\r\nOur webmasters Jauyeu (<a href=\"mailto:Jauyeulai@yahoo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Jauyeulai@yahoo.com</a>) &amp; Steven (<a href=\"mailto:tengkolien@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">tengkolien@gmail.com</a>) are looking for new pictures for slide show on MCS website. Our current slide show subject is \"<span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy\". Our next slide show subject will be \"Taiwan Scenery by MCS parents\". If you have any pictures about Taiwan that you would like to share, you may send the files to JauYeu &amp; Steven by the end of the month. This is a great opportunity to share with our kids the beauty of Taiwan island.\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS communication - 10/24/09',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-102409','','','2010-01-22 01:50:03','2010-01-22 05:50:03','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=15',0,'post','',0),(16,1,'2010-01-22 01:50:46','2010-01-22 05:50:46','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nThis Saturday 10/31 is Halloween. We will held a Halloween parade during the break starting around 2:30pm. Treats will be passed out by school staff. We encourage all students and parents to wear Halloween costume. Considering that we have very young kids in the school, please do not wear mask, toy weapons (knife, gun..etc) and any bloody stuff.\r\n\r\nMr. Jauyeu Lai will take pictures for this activity and post them on MCS website. This year we will have a Halloween costume contest. 12 students will be selected to compete in the following 3 categories. The winner in each category will get a $20 gift card award.\r\n\r\n1. Best Halloween costume\r\n2. Most creative costume design\r\n3. Most green costume design (utilize of recycle material, waste, ...)\r\n\r\nJesse Wei, Tracy Wu and TingWei Lwo will be our judges. They will start the judging event around 1:30pm. So, don\'t wait till the parade to dress up the costume. We will try to begin the award ceremony at end of the parade.\r\n\r\nStarting this Saturday is our <span>Chinese</span> reading month. Students are encouraged to read <span>Chinese</span> books, watch <span>Chinese</span> movies....   Students who complete 240 minutes reading will be given a $5 reward.  Your children\'s  classroom teachers have books to share with the students. Recording sheet is  attached.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know if you have any suggestions.\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 10/31/09',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-103109','','','2010-01-22 01:50:46','2010-01-22 05:50:46','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=16',0,'post','',0),(17,1,'2010-01-22 01:50:26','2010-01-22 05:50:26','','MCS Communication - 10/31/09',0,'','inherit','open','open','','16-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:50:26','2010-01-22 05:50:26','',16,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=17',0,'revision','',0),(18,1,'2010-01-22 01:51:38','2010-01-22 05:51:38','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nWe had a wonderful Halloween parade and contest last week. I\'d like to congratulate the three winners: <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">\r\n\r\nCeleste Lai</span> - 1st grade (Best Halloween Costume), <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">\r\nJessica Wu</span> - Ma 11 (Most Green Costume Design), <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">\r\nEric Wu</span> - Senior class (Most Creative Costume Design).\r\n\r\nEach winner received a $20 gift card. We also have 12 students selected into the final contest. Each of them received a $5 gift card and a goodie bag. I trust that most kids and parents had a great time in participating and taking pictures. If you have any good pictures that would like to share, please send the pictures to JauYeu (<a href=\"mailto:jauyeulai@yahoo.com\" target=\"_blank\">jauyeulai@yahoo.com</a>) &amp; Steven (<a href=\"mailto:tengkolien@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">tengkolien@gmail.com</a>). They will post them on MCS website. Jauyeu Lai has  already posted the pictures he took on our website: <a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>\r\nYou may also find new class pictures in the \"class activity\" link and new job openings.\r\n\r\nWe sold $935 tickets for the Double-Tenth concert. Although MCS is not the biggest <span>Chinese</span> school among the local 4, we have sold most tickets comparing to other schools. <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">We were awarded $861 </span>from the Double-Tenth organization committe. Thanks for all parents participating this event!\r\n<div><strong>Reminder - Reading month starts</strong></div>\r\n<div>Students are encouraged to read <span>Chinese</span> books, watch <span>Chinese</span> movies....  Students who complete 240 minutes will be given $5 reward.  Your  children\'s classroom teachers have books to share with the students. Recording  sheets have been passed out last week.</div>\r\nThis week <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">方漢華 and Mike Freeman</span> are parents on duty. Please report to Wen Chang at 1:30pm.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">School directory is ready.</span> Don\'t forget to pick it up this Saturday at Parents room. Thanks for the effort from our MCS parents and staff, especially Jauyeu Lai, who put in a lot of efforts to compile the directory contents and collect Ads. The Ads income is not only able to cover the directory expense but also contribute a few hundred dollars to our school budget.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Hunan Hunan</span> will be at our school again this Saturday. There will be a new dish  available \"drunken chicken\". You may call to put in orders or if you  have any questions, before Friday 9:00, (313) 398-0939.\r\n\r\nThanks for your continuous support and together, we will make MCS a fun and exciting place for our kids to learn <span>Chinese</span>.\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 11/7/09',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-11709','','','2010-01-22 01:51:38','2010-01-22 05:51:38','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=18',0,'post','',0),(19,1,'2010-01-22 01:51:19','2010-01-22 05:51:19','','MCS Communication - 11/7/09',0,'','inherit','open','open','','18-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:51:19','2010-01-22 05:51:19','',18,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=19',0,'revision','',0),(20,1,'2010-01-22 01:53:19','2010-01-22 05:53:19','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nLast school year our ex-principal Hou made an announcement to promote teaching and reciting 弟子規. Below is an extract from her e-mail on 3/9/2009:\r\n\r\n******************************\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-size-adjust: inherit; font-stretch: inherit;\" valign=\"top\">***********************************************************************\r\n<div>Dear parents:</div>\r\n<div>I am very happy to inform you that last Saturday, <span style=\"background-color: #ffff40;\">our school received a very generous donation  from a 王老先生.</span> His grand-daughter was once student in our school.  He is  donating his money to help promote the <span>Chinese</span> language and <span>Chinese</span> culture.  We  are <span>truly</span> grateful to his generosity.  In his honor, some teachers  in our school will start to add some old teachings from 弟子規 in their classes.</div>\r\n<div>I put together a PowerPoint presentation for 讀經班.  I presented it on  2/28 but not many parents showed up.  I think this will also be a good  opportunity for kids to learn some old teachings from our ancestor.  I intent to  make it a fun class with the goal of presenting the result in next year\'s New  Year Program.  If you are interested, please take a look at the attached  PowerPoint.  Students who can memorize the whole thing will be awarded $100.  Please let me know if you are interested in signing up your child/ren for this  class.\r\n*****************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nEx-principal Hou made an attempt to assemble an extra-curriculum class for students to learn 弟子規. Attached file contains details of her proposal. Due to many reasons, the class couldn\'t attract enough students to become official. However, some students may have made an effort to recite the whole article and might be very disappointed if the $100 award is gone with the class. In our teachers meeting held last month, we decided to continue the commitment of offering $100 awrad to students who can recite the complete article 弟子規.\r\n\r\nStudents may come forward to recite the complete 弟子規 in front of our committe (教務主任, 校長) on 1/30/2010 at parents lounge after regular class. We will award $100 in the New Year Celebration Party (2/6/2010) to students who memorize the complete article and recite fluently. Students who intend to participate in this reciting event should notify their teacher before end of the fall semeter.\r\n\r\nThis Saturday Hunan-Hunan 双湘园 will come to school again with 滷味.雞棑便當.糯米大肠.粽子.醉雞.臭豆腐.肉圆.碗粿.\r\n\r\nParents on duty<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">: <span style=\"color: #0000ff; font-weight: bold;\">馮安強, 積博思</span></span>\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody></table>','MCS Communication - 11/14/2009',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-11142009','','','2010-01-22 01:53:19','2010-01-22 05:53:19','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=20',0,'post','',0),(21,1,'2010-01-22 01:53:00','2010-01-22 05:53:00','','MCS Communication - 11/14/2009',0,'','inherit','open','open','','20-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:53:00','2010-01-22 05:53:00','',20,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=21',0,'revision','',0),(22,1,'2010-01-22 01:54:08','2010-01-22 05:54:08','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nEnjoy a quiet week before Thanksgiving!\r\n\r\nParents on duty this Saturday : <span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #ff0000;\">蓋濟民, 王衛華</span>\r\n\r\nNew job opening for FEA analyst is posted on MCS website.\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 11/21/09',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-112109','','','2010-01-22 01:54:08','2010-01-22 05:54:08','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=22',0,'post','',0),(23,1,'2010-01-22 01:53:54','2010-01-22 05:53:54','','MCS Communication - 11/21/09',0,'','inherit','open','open','','22-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:53:54','2010-01-22 05:53:54','',22,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=23',0,'revision','',0),(24,1,'2010-01-22 01:54:44','2010-01-22 05:54:44','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nI hope every student has enjoyed a wonderful Thanksgiving holiday and is ready for the coming <span>Chinese</span> school this Saturday. Don\'t forget that it\'s time to turn in the reading sheet for $5 reading award.\r\n\r\nThis Saturday we will have teaching staff meeting after school. Teachers need to attend. Parents are also welcome to participate for any suggestions.\r\n\r\nParents on duty: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">侯禹任,  許呈維</span>\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 12/5/2009',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-1252009','','','2010-01-22 01:54:44','2010-01-22 05:54:44','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=24',0,'post','',0),(25,1,'2010-01-22 01:54:29','2010-01-22 05:54:29','','MCS Communication - 12/5/2009',0,'','inherit','open','open','','24-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:54:29','2010-01-22 05:54:29','',24,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=25',0,'revision','',0),(26,1,'2010-01-22 01:55:29','2010-01-22 05:55:29','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\n12/12 is the last school day of the year. Since we won\'t be seeing you after this Saturday, I and our MCS staff wish everyone Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year! If you plan to have a trip during holidays, please place your family\'s safety in mind all the time while enjoying your get-away. In the past few years there were several ski accidents happened to our school\'s friends and families. So, have a fun and safe holidays!\r\n\r\nOur parents on duty this Saturday: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">周治太</span> &amp; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">郭友信</span>\r\n\r\nThis Saturday we will start the selection of student hosts for 2/6/2010 <span>Chinese</span> New Year Celebration Party. Any students in 7th grades and above, are encouraged to participate. We will interview the students on 2:30pm at classroom 2401. The students will be interviewed with 2 questions:\r\n\r\n1. How do you introduce yourself to the public?\r\n2. Why you would like to be the host and what\'s your qualification?\r\n\r\nThis year we will have 6 students and 2 teachers to host our New Year Celebration. I believe our teachers have already informed some students to attend the selection. This is a good opportunity for student to learn public speech and on-stage performing.\r\n\r\nOur New Year Celebration will be held at Livonia Stevenson High School on 2/6/2010 Saturday. Program runs from 3pm to 5:30pm with performance from each class and parents. Parents who may be interested in performing may contact either Jim Yang or Patti Fu to be included in the program. Dinner starts at 6pm along with several games for students to play. This year, we decided to discount our dinner ticket to the following price to counteract the Michigan recession (or depression based on who you talked to):\r\n\r\nAdult ticket: $5, kids  under 12: $3, kids under 3: free (Tickets will be on sale early next year)\r\n\r\nOur PTA Chairman Jim Yang has worked out dinner menu and restaurant with class representatives. You may ask your class representative for details. We welcome you and your whole family to join to celebrate the <span>Chinese</span> Tiger year.\r\n\r\nAs in the past years, we welcome company sponsors for this New Year event. Please let me know if you or anyone you know that may donate funds or gifts for this event. A few years ago Ameriplus financial company helped to offload part of the school budget burden in this event. I sure hope we have the same luck this year.\r\n\r\nNote: Students completed the reading month requirements will be awarded this week in each class.\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 12/12/2009',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-12122009','','','2010-01-22 01:55:29','2010-01-22 05:55:29','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=26',0,'post','',0),(27,1,'2010-01-22 01:55:12','2010-01-22 05:55:12','','MCS Communication - 12/12/2009',0,'','inherit','open','open','','26-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:55:12','2010-01-22 05:55:12','',26,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=27',0,'revision','',0),(28,1,'2010-01-22 01:56:13','2010-01-22 05:56:13','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nHappy 2010! I wish you all have enjoyed a very pleasant holiday and are ready for a fresh start of the new year.\r\n\r\nThis Saturday we have several things going:\r\n\r\n1. The Fall semester ends on 1/23 and Spring semester begins on 1/30. We will start student registration this Saturday. Don\'t forget to bring your check book to the school. Like in the Fall semester, we still offer $50 tuition rebate for every new student you recruit.\r\n\r\n2. We will start ticket sale for 2/6 New Year celebration dinner. To encourage your participation along with consideration of current depressed economy, the ticket price is discounted to $5 for adult and $3 for kids under 12. PTA chair Jim Yang has selected a <span>Chinese</span> restaurant famous for traditional Taiwanese food to host the buffet. Dinner menu was decided by all class representatives. Please contact them for details.\r\n\r\n3. This year we will have both adults and students to host the New Year Celebration. The following students were interviewed and selected as student hosts: Irene Li, Jessica Wu, Justin Hsieh, Eric Tang, Timothy Lu and Eric Li. These students should meet with teachers Patty Fu and WeiLi Yang after regular class to start practice.\r\n\r\n4. During New Year Celebration we will award scholarship to students ranked top 25% in the class (the rule was published in previous MCS communication). Please encourage your kids to work hard in the next 3 weeks to improve his or her grades (listed in the student record sheet that most teachers provided to you from time to time).\r\n\r\n5. Parents on duty: 呂思平, 藍任昇\r\n\r\n6. Hunan-Hunan will deliver your <span>Chinese</span> food orders to parents room every 2nd and 4th week. So, your may pick up your food orders this Saturday.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know if you have any questions or  comments.\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 1/9/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-192010','','','2010-01-22 01:56:13','2010-01-22 05:56:13','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=28',0,'post','',0),(29,1,'2010-01-22 01:55:56','2010-01-22 05:55:56','','MCS Communication - 1/9/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','28-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:55:56','2010-01-22 05:55:56','',28,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=29',0,'revision','',0),(30,1,'2010-01-22 01:56:44','2010-01-22 05:56:44','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nReminders:\r\n\r\n1. The Fall semester ends on 1/23 and Spring semester begins on 1/30. We will continue student r