iv>Our New Year Celebration Party starts on 3PM at Stevenson High School followed with dinner party at 6PM. Program schedule has been posted on MCS website for your review. You may also find pictures taken from last year\'s New Year Party in the school Album under directory \"sly\". Since the New Year Party is organized and prepared by all of us, students, parents and school staff, I believe we will have great fun together to celebrate the start of Chinese Tiger Year.</div>\n<div>Regarding to the recitation of \"弟子規\", one student recited 95% of the book last week. He may finish the complete book if there are more time for prepration. Several students also expressed interest to recite the complete book if there are more time allowed for preparation. Therefore, to encourage more student participation, we will extend the deadline till end of May. Students who may recite the complete \"弟子規\" at the end of May will be awarded $100 at the school Graduation Ceremony in June.</div>\n<div>Spring semester registration has ended. We have 3 new students and lost 6 students for various reasons. Total student count is 108 for this semester. Please offer your welcome to the new faces when you meet them in the school or in the New Year Party.</div>\n<div>Have a great weekend!</div>\n<div>Best Regards</div>\n<div>Alex Tang</div>\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 2/6/2010',0,'','draft','open','open','','','','','2010-02-04 23:51:15','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=37',0,'post','',0),(38,1,'2010-02-04 23:52:14','2010-02-05 03:52:14','Dear MCS parents,\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nHappy Chinese New Year and no school for this Saturday and next Saturday!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nOur New Year Celebration Party starts on 3PM at Stevenson High School followed with dinner party at 6PM. Program schedule has been posted on MCS website for your review. You may also find pictures taken from last year\'s New Year Party in the school Album under directory \"sly\". Since the New Year Party is organized and prepared by all of us, students, parents and school staff, I believe we will have great fun together to celebrate the start of Chinese Tiger Year.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nRegarding to the recitation of \"弟子規\", one student recited 95% of the book last week. He may finish the complete book if there are more time for prepration. Several students also expressed interest to recite the complete book if there are more time allowed for preparation. Therefore, to encourage more student participation, we will extend the deadline till end of May. Students who may recite the complete \"弟子規\" at the end of May will be awarded $100 at the school Graduation Ceremony in June.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nSpring semester registration has ended. We have 3 new students and lost 6 students for various reasons. Total student count is 108 for this semester. Please offer your welcome to the new faces when you meet them in the school or in the New Year Party.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nHave a great weekend!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 2/6/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-262010','','','2010-02-04 23:52:14','2010-02-05 03:52:14','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=38',0,'post','',0),(39,1,'2010-02-04 23:51:36','2010-02-05 03:51:36','<h1>MCS Communication - 2/6/2010</h1>','MCS Communication - 2/6/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','38-revision','','','2010-02-04 23:51:36','2010-02-05 03:51:36','',38,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=39',0,'revision','',0),(40,1,'2010-02-04 23:53:26','2010-02-05 03:53:26','Dear MCS parents,\n<div>\n\nHappy Chinese New Year and no school for this Saturday and next Saturday!\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nOur New Year Celebration Party starts on 3PM at Stevenson High School followed with dinner party at 6PM. Program schedule has been posted on MCS website for your review. You may also find pictures taken from last year\'s New Year Party in the school Album under directory \"sly\". Since the New Year Party is organized and prepared by all of us, students, parents and school staff, I believe we will have great fun together to celebrate the start of Chinese Tiger Year.\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nRegarding to the recitation of \"弟子規\", one student recited 95% of the book last week. He may finish the complete book if there are more time for prepration. Several students also expressed interest to recite the complete book if there are more time allowed for preparation. Therefore, to encourage more student participation, we will extend the deadline till end of May. Students who may recite the complete \"弟子規\" at the end of May will be awarded $100 at the school Graduation Ceremony in June.\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nSpring semester registration has ended. We have 3 new students and lost 6 students for various reasons. Total student count is 108 for this semester. Please offer your welcome to the new faces when you meet them in the school or in the New Year Party.\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nHave a great weekend!\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nBest Regards\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nAlex Tang\n\n</div>\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 2/6/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','38-autosave','','','2010-02-04 23:53:26','2010-02-05 03:53:26','',38,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=40',0,'revision','',0),(41,1,'2010-02-19 00:55:12','2010-02-19 04:55:12','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nHappy Chinese New Year!\r\n\r\nI wish everyone has enjoyed our New Year Party and a quiet mid-winter break weekend. Thanks for your participation! I heard a lot of compliments on this year\'s dinner food. Please give a loud applause to our PTA chair - Jim Yang. He not only coordinated the preparation work of this event, but also contributed his professional singing performance during the party. If you are interested to be the next white-horse-prince, you may sign up for his extra-curriculum guitar class this weekend.\r\n\r\nWe also want to thank the two students that performed the talk show:  鄺紹耘 &amp; 王淨德. and our six student hosts: 李藹玲,李祥, 唐涵中, 謝耀廷,吳品萱,呂詠恩. This Year 蔡耀霆 volunteered to paint the big tiger for our stage decoration again. He painted a big Mouse for MCS 2008 New Year Party decoration. Due to time conflict, he won\'t be attending MCS this semester. Thank you 耀霆 and wish you the best for your future!\r\n\r\nOur two beautiful hosts: Patty Fu and WeiLi Yang devoted a lot effort and time to make  the Party full of fun. I can\'t say enough to express my appreciation. This Saturday we will start selling the New Year Party DVD recorded by JauYeu Lai for $5 a set. You may own a long lasting memory of your kids and performance of our beautiful hosts. So don\'t forget to bring your cash for it.\r\n\r\nWe need more kids to participate in the extra-curriculum class and activity. The  following classes are still open for enrollment:\r\n1. Lion dance team - learn to be part of Chinese culture with a group of young &amp; energetic Chinese students.\r\n2. English writing for SAT - still need a couple more students that may want to sharpen the English writing skills\r\n3. Guitar class -  Want to impress your friends with the guitar music? Our PTA chair Jim Yang who used to perform guitar and singing back in Taiwan will guide you step by step towards your dream\r\n\r\nOK, our parents on duty this week are: 馬國驥,               江政承\r\n\r\nDon\'t forget to visit our web site from time to time for new learning &amp; job opportunity.\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 2/20/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-2202010','','','2010-02-19 00:55:12','2010-02-19 04:55:12','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=41',0,'post','',0),(42,1,'2010-02-19 00:55:07','2010-02-19 04:55:07','Dear MCS parents,\n\nHappy Chinese New Year!\n\nI wish everyone has enjoyed our New Year Party and a quiet mid-winter break weekend. Thanks for your participation! I heard a lot of compliments on this year\'s dinner food. Please give a loud applause to our PTA chair - Jim Yang. He not only coordinated the preparation work of this event, but also contributed his professional singing performance during the party. If you are interested to be the next white-horse-prince, you may sign up for his extra-curriculum guitar class this weekend.\n\nWe also want to thank the two students that performed the talk show:  鄺紹耘 &amp; 王淨德. and our six student hosts: 李藹玲,李祥, 唐涵中, 謝耀廷,吳品萱,呂詠恩. This Year 蔡耀霆 volunteered to paint the big tiger for our stage decoration again. He painted a big Mouse for MCS 2008 New Year Party decoration. Due to time conflict, he won\'t be attending MCS this semester. Thank you 耀霆 and wish you the best for your future!\n\nOur two beautiful hosts: Patty Fu and WeiLi Yang devoted a lot effort and time to make  the Party full of fun. I can\'t say enough to express my appreciation. This Saturday we will start selling the New Year Party DVD recorded by JauYeu Lai for $5 a set. You may own a long lasting memory of your kids and performance of our beautiful hosts. So don\'t forget to bring your cash for it.\n\nWe need more kids to participate in the extra-curriculum class and activity. The  following classes are still open for enrollment:\n1. Lion dance team - learn to be part of Chinese culture with a group of young &amp; energetic Chinese students.\n2. English writing for SAT - still need a couple more students that may want to sharpen the English writing skills\n3. Guitar class -  Want to impress your friends with the guitar music? Our PTA chair Jim Yang who used to perform guitar and singing back in Taiwan will guide you step by step towards your dream\n\nOK, our parents on duty this week are: 馬國驥,               江政承\n\nDon\'t forget to visit our web site from time to time for new learning &amp; job opportunity.\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 2/20/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','41-revision','','','2010-02-19 00:55:07','2010-02-19 04:55:07','',41,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=42',0,'revision','',0),(43,1,'2010-02-27 01:41:47','2010-02-27 05:41:47','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nAs shown in the following extracts from our PTA chair Jim Yang\'s e-mail:\r\n+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\r\n各位家長代表,\r\n\r\n本人因工作關係將於三月初回台, 考量到接下來家長會長的工作任務無法續任,\r\n所以決定將於本周六2/27 ,1:40 pm 召開臨時家長大會介紹新任家長會長劉怡均小姐(Julia),同時她也將接任一年級班家長代表的工作.\r\n本人在此特別感謝劉小姐的幫忙 ,也懇請各位代表能夠多多支持她, 再次感謝各位-\r\n+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\r\n\r\nJim will pursue a new career in Taiwan starting next month. Even though his term in MCS was short, Jim\'s contribution to MCS is well recognized and visible. For instance, as we put it on the New Year Party DVD, his decoration at central stage, his guitar and singing performance, his arrangements on the dinner menu, plus all behind the scene coordinations. Thanks Jim and we all wish you to become a millionaire entrepreneur soon.\r\n\r\nWe also want to thank Julia Liu 劉怡均小姐 for her willingness to fill in Jim\'s position. Julia has been actively assisting 1st grade teacher in the classroom. I believe her passion to make MCS a better place for our kids will sure earn everyone\'s support. Please offer her your support when you meet her on the hallway this Saturday.\r\n\r\nReminders of the week:\r\n---