//michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=48',0,'revision','',0),(49,1,'2010-03-18 23:59:23','2010-03-19 03:59:23','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nI\'m glad to announce that Lisa Hou, MCS 2009 principal, will offer a seminar to you this week. She will cover investment vehicles that are available to the parents for setting up education funds, such as MET, UGMA, 529, MESP, etc. Please come to the Parents Lounge to enjoy Lisa\'s sharing of her knowledge and experience on these subject. The seminar will begin around 1:40pm and last for about an hour.\r\n\r\nThere was an incident happened in one classroom last week. The plastic cover of a ceiling light somehow fell to the floor. It\'s fortunate that no one got hurt. The incident was reported to the Madonna Univ. immediately. I\'m not sure whether the Univ. has examined all ceiling lights or not. However, please just take a cautious step in the classroom and report to us should you find any loosening ceiling light cover.\r\n\r\nParents on duty: 余宏鴻, 陳德修\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication 3/20/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-3202010','','','2010-03-18 23:59:23','2010-03-19 03:59:23','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=49',0,'post','',0),(50,1,'2010-03-18 23:59:07','2010-03-19 03:59:07','','MCS Communication 3/20/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','49-revision','','','2010-03-18 23:59:07','2010-03-19 03:59:07','',49,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=50',0,'revision','',0),(51,1,'2010-04-03 23:21:19','2010-04-04 03:21:19','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nReminder: No school this weekend! Enjoy a spring break week but don\'t forget to prepare for the school speech contest on 4/17. Next school day - 4/10/2010.\r\n\r\nAttached please find information about a Chinese culture learning camp for this summer.\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipa